ChatGPT said:
You're on the right track: your Java program merges two arrays and attempts to find the median. However, there are a few issues that need fixing:

âŒ Problems in Your Code:
â— Median logic is incorrect for even-length arrays:

java
Copy
Edit
int result = num[num.length/2] + num[num.length/2 + 1];
This doesn't compute the average â€” it adds the two middle elements, and also uses a wrong index (off-by-one error).

â— You're always printing two values â€” one inside the if block and another after it.

â— The function returns 0 always, which doesnâ€™t make sense for a method named findMedianSortedArrays.

âœ… Fixes & Clean Version:
java
Copy
Edit
import java.util.*;

class Main {
    public static double findMedianSortedArrays(int[] nums1, int[] nums2) {
        int[] num = new int[nums1.length + nums2.length];

        // Copy nums1 and nums2 into num[]
        for (int i = 0; i < nums1.length; i++) {
            num[i] = nums1[i];
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < nums2.length; i++) {
            num[nums1.length + i] = nums2[i];
        }

        // Sort merged array
        Arrays.sort(num);

        // Find median
        int n = num.length;
        double median;
        if (n % 2 == 0) {
            median = (num[n / 2 - 1] + num[n / 2]) / 2.0;  // Correct average
        } else {
            median = num[n / 2];
        }

        System.out.println("Median: " + median);
        return median;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);

        ArrayList<Integer> a = new ArrayList<>();
        System.out.println("Enter elements of first array (-1 to stop):");
        while (true) {
            int v = s.nextInt();
            if (v == -1) break;
            a.add(v);
        }

        ArrayList<Integer> b = new ArrayList<>();
        System.out.println("Enter elements of second array (-1 to stop):");
        while (true) {
            int d = s.nextInt();
            if (d == -1) break;
            b.add(d);
        }

        // Convert ArrayLists to int arrays
        int[] e = new int[a.size()];
        for (int i = 0; i < a.size(); i++) {
            e[i] = a.get(i);
        }

        int[] f = new int[b.size()];
        for (int i = 0; i < b.size(); i++) {
            f[i] = b.get(i);
        }

        findMedianSortedArrays(e, f);
        s.close();
    }
}
