ChatGPT said:
You're trying to print a pattern with stars (*) and underscores (_), which is a great Java exercise â€” but your code has some Python-style syntax like:

java
Copy
Edit
"_" * i
"*" * n
This is invalid in Java! Java doesn't allow multiplying strings like Python.

âŒ Problems in Your Code
"_" * i and "*".repeat(i) â€” in Java, you must use .repeat() method (Java 11+).

You're calling star(a) from main, but it's a non-static method, and main is static.

The logic inside the loop is a bit unclear â€” it's not printing a consistent pattern.

âœ… Fixed Version Using Java 11+ (String.repeat())
Here's a corrected version with a simple pyramid/box pattern idea:

java
Copy
Edit
import java.util.*;

public class Teja {
    public void star(int n) {
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            // Print leading spaces or underscores
            String underscores = "_".repeat(n - i - 1);
            
            // Print pattern
            if (i == 0) {
                System.out.println(underscores + "*");
            } else if (i == n - 1) {
                System.out.println("*".repeat(2 * n - 1));  // Base full of stars
            } else {
                String middle = "_".repeat(2 * i - 1);
                System.out.println(underscores + "*" + middle + "*");
            }
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);
        int a = s.nextInt();
        Teja t = new Teja(); // Create object to call non-static method
        t.star(a);
        s.close();
    }
}
