ğŸš¨ Problems in Your Code:
âŒ 1. Variables c and d get redefined in each loop
They are not preserved across iterations.

Also, in System.out.println(a.subSequence(i, c)); and a.subSequence(i, d);, at the end of the loop, i is already equal to a.length() â€” invalid!

âŒ 2. The subSequence(i, c) usage is incorrect
String.subSequence(start, end) requires that start <= end.

Since i == a.length() at the end, a.subSequence(i, c) may throw StringIndexOutOfBoundsException.

âŒ 3. Logic is unclear and incomplete
The inner for loops attempt to check if substring is palindrome, but:

