No check is stored if a longer palindrome is found

No variable is keeping track of the longest palindrome

âœ… How to Fix It?
If your goal is to find the longest palindromic substring, the best fix is to use a center expansion method like we saw earlier.

But if you want to manually implement the palindrome check using two-pointer logic, hereâ€™s a basic example to build upon:

âœ… Example: Check Longest Palindromic Substring (Two-Pointer Brute Force)
java
Copy
Edit
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static boolean isPalindrome(String s, int left, int right) {
        while (left < right) {
            if (s.charAt(left) != s.charAt(right))
                return false;
            left++;
            right--;
        }
        return true;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);
        String input = s.nextLine();
        String result = "";

        for (int i = 0; i < input.length(); i++) {
            for (int j = i; j < input.length(); j++) {
                if (isPalindrome(input, i, j)) {
                    String sub = input.substring(i, j + 1);
                    if (sub.length() > result.length()) {
                        result = sub;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println("Longest Palindromic Substring: " + result);
        s.close();
    }
}
