Great! Here's a deep explanation of Java Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) with key concepts and example programs:

ğŸ”‘ Core OOP Concepts in Java:
1. Class & Object
Class: A blueprint for creating objects. Defines attributes (fields) and behavior (methods).

Object: An instance of a class.

java
Copy
Edit
class Car {
    String color;
    void drive() {
        System.out.println("Car is driving");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Car myCar = new Car();  // Object creation
        myCar.color = "Red";
        myCar.drive();
    }
}
2. Encapsulation
Wrapping data and methods together.

Use private fields and public getters/setters.

java
Copy
Edit
class Student {
    private int age;

    public void setAge(int a) {
        if (a > 0) age = a;
    }

    public int getAge() {
        return age;
    }
}
3. Inheritance
One class inherits fields and methods from another using extends.

java
Copy
Edit
class Animal {
    void eat() {
        System.out.println("Eating...");
    }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
    void bark() {
        System.out.println("Barking...");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Dog d = new Dog();
        d.eat();  // inherited
        d.bark(); // own method
    }
}
4. Polymorphism
One method behaves differently based on context.

a) Compile-Time (Method Overloading)
java
Copy
Edit
class MathUtils {
    int add(int a, int b) { return a + b; }
    int add(int a, int b, int c) { return a + b + c; }
}
b) Runtime (Method Overriding)
java
Copy
Edit
class Animal {
    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Some sound");
    }
}

class Cat extends Animal {
    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Meow");
    }
}
5. Abstraction
Hiding internal details and showing only essentials using abstract classes or interfaces.

a) Abstract Class
java
Copy
Edit
abstract class Shape {
    abstract void draw();
}

class Circle extends Shape {
    void draw() {
        System.out.println("Drawing Circle");
    }
}
b) Interface
java
Copy
Edit
interface Flyable {
    void fly();
}

class Bird implements Flyable {
    public void fly() {
        System.out.println("Flying high");
    }
}
ğŸŒŸ Object-Oriented Features in Practice:
java
Copy
Edit
interface Engine {
    void start();
}

abstract class Vehicle {
    String brand = "Generic";

    abstract void run();
}

class Bike extends Vehicle implements Engine {
    public void start() {
        System.out.println(brand + " bike started");
    }

    void run() {
        System.out.println("Bike is running");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Bike b = new Bike();
        b.brand = "Yamaha";
        b.start();
        b.run();
    }
}
