ChatGPT said:
In the same program, you can access private fields of a class only through getters and setters, even inside the same .java fileâ€”as long as it's from outside the class that declares them.

âœ… Letâ€™s break it down with a full example:
java
Copy
Edit
// Class with encapsulated fields
class Student {
    private String name;
    private int marks;

    // Setter for name
    public void setName(String n) {
        name = n;
    }

    // Getter for name
    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }

    // Setter for marks
    public void setMarks(int m) {
        if (m >= 0 && m <= 100) {
            marks = m;
        } else {
            System.out.println("Invalid marks!");
        }
    }

    // Getter for marks
    public int getMarks() {
        return marks;
    }
}
ğŸ‘‡ Access in the same program (same file):
java
Copy
