    return str;
} else {
    return compressed.toString();
}
If the compressed version is longer than the original string, it doesnâ€™t make sense to compress, so we return the original.

Otherwise, return the compressed string.

ğŸ§  Example: "aabcccccaaa"
Step-by-step:
'a' appears 2 times â†’ a2

'b' appears 1 time â†’ b1

'c' appears 5 times â†’ c5

'a' appears 3 times â†’ a3

So, final compressed = a2b1c5a3
Length = 8 < Original length = 11 â†’ Return a2b1c5a3

ğŸ§  Example: "abc"
Each letter appears once â†’ a1b1c1

Compressed length = 6 > Original length = 3 â†’ Return abc

