ChatGPT said:
Your Java code has multiple issues, and I'll walk you through each one and provide a corrected version with a clear explanation of what's wrong.

âŒ Issues in Your Code:
You named your class String â€“ this conflicts with Java's built-in java.lang.String class.

â›” Don't name your class String. It's a reserved and commonly used class in Java.

Constructors can't return values â€“ lines like return n*n; inside a constructor are invalid.

â›” Constructors are not allowed to have return statements with values.

You tried to use the result of a constructor as if it returns a value, which it doesn't.

âœ… Corrected Code Example (Constructor Overloading with Square class):
java
Copy
Edit
import java.util.*;

class Square {
    Square() {
        System.out.println("Default constructor called.");
    }

    Square(int n) {
        System.out.println("Square of " + n + " is " + (n * n));
    }
}

class Str extends Square {
    Str() {
        super(); // Calls Square()
        System.out.println("Str class default constructor.");
    }

    Str(int b) {
        super(b); // Calls Square(int)
        System.out.println("Str class parameterized constructor.");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);
        int a = s.nextInt();

        Str obj1 = new Str();       // Calls default constructors
        Str obj2 = new Str(a);      // Calls parameterized constructors

        s.close();
    }
}
ğŸ§¾ Sample Output (if input is 5):
