You said:
Read an integer and print if it is a power of 2 using logical operators


ChatGPT said:
To check whether a number is a power of 2 using logical and bitwise operators, you can use the fact that:

A number n is a power of 2 if and only if n > 0 and (n & (n - 1)) == 0.

âœ… Java Code Using Logical and Bitwise Operators:
java
Copy
Edit
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = s.nextInt();

        if (n > 0 && (n & (n - 1)) == 0) {
            System.out.println("Power of 2");
        } else {
            System.out.println("Not a power of 2");
        }

        s.close();
    }
}
ğŸ” Explanation:
n > 0 â€“ A power of 2 must be positive.

n & (n - 1) â€“ This checks if there is only one set bit in the binary representation of n.

For example:

8 â†’ 1000 â†’ 8 & 7 = 1000 & 0111 = 0000 â†’ âœ…

10 â†’ 1010 â†’ 10 & 9 = 1010 & 1001 = 1000 â†’ âŒ

âœ… Sample Output:
makefile
Copy
Edit
Input: 8
Output: Power of 2

Input: 10
Output: Not a power of 2
