ChatGPT said:
You're very close! But your current code has two main issues:

âŒ Mistakes:
Flag f is not reset to 0 for every number. Once itâ€™s set to 1, it stays that way for all following numbers.

Incorrect loop condition: j < Math.sqrt(a[i]) should be j <= Math.sqrt(a[i]). Also, j should be at least 2.

âœ… Corrected Code:
java
Copy
Edit
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = s.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = s.nextInt();
        }

        int m = 1;
        boolean foundPrime = false;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int f = 0;
            if (a[i] <= 1) continue; // Skip 0, 1, and negatives

            for (int j = 2; j <= Math.sqrt(a[i]); j++) {
                if (a[i] % j == 0) {
                    f = 1;
                    break;
                }
            }

            if (f == 0) {
                m *= a[i];
                foundPrime = true;
            }
        }

        if (foundPrime)
            System.out.println(m);
        else
            System.out.println("No prime numbers found");

        s.close();
    }
}
ğŸ” Notes:
f is reset inside the outer loop.

continue skips numbers â‰¤ 1 (not prime).

