ChatGPT said:
Your Java program has two issues:

âŒ Problems:
break; after return; â€“ Not needed. Once return is called, the method exits.

Typo in chatAt(0) â€“ should be charAt(0).

âœ… Corrected Code:
java
Copy
Edit
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static int Calci(int n, int m, char c) {
        switch (c) {
            case '+':
                return n + m;
            case '-':
                return n - m;
            case '*':
                return n * m;
            case '/':
                return m != 0 ? n / m : 0; // prevent divide by zero
            default:
                return 0; // invalid operator
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = s.nextInt();
        int m = s.nextInt();
        char c = s.next().charAt(0); // Fixed typo

        System.out.println(Calci(n, m, c));
        s.close();
    }
}
