ChatGPT said:
Your current Java code has several issues:

âŒ Issues:
Youâ€™re trying to reverse a String using n.reverse() â€” but n is a String, and String doesn't have a reverse() method.

You're assigning a String to a StringBuilder (s = n.reverse().toString();) â€” which is a type mismatch.

Youâ€™re comparing StringBuilder (s) and String (n) using == â€” which checks for reference equality, not value equality.

You named the method check, but itâ€™s supposed to check for palindrome, not whether a string is prime (as isprime might imply).

âœ… Corrected & Complete Code:
This program checks if the given string is a palindrome.

java
Copy
Edit
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    static boolean isPalindrome(String n) {
        StringBuilder reversed = new StringBuilder(n);
        reversed.reverse();
        return n.equals(reversed.toString());
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);
        String input = s.nextLine();
        
        if (isPalindrome(input)) {
            System.out.println("Palindrome");
        } else {
            System.out.println("Not Palindrome");
        }

        s.close();
    }
}
