You said:
read a name,age,grade and modify with new name like that in encapsulation


ChatGPT said:
In encapsulation, we use private variables with getter and setter methods to read and modify values like name, age, and grade. Here's a full example in Java that demonstrates this concept:

âœ… Java Code Using Encapsulation
java
Copy
Edit
import java.util.*;

class Student {
    // Private data members
    private String name;
    private int age;
    private char grade;

    // Constructor
    public Student(String name, int age, char grade) {
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
        this.grade = grade;
    }

    // Getter methods
    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }
    public int getAge() {
        return age;
    }
    public char getGrade() {
        return grade;
    }

    // Setter methods
    public void setName(String name) {
        this.name = name;
    }
    public void setAge(int age) {
        this.age = age;
    }
    public void setGrade(char grade) {
        this.grade = grade;
    }

    // Display method
    public void display() {
        System.out.println("Name: " + name);
        System.out.println("Age: " + age);
        System.out.println("Grade: " + grade);
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);

        // Read input
        System.out.print("Enter name: ");
        String name = s.nextLine();

        System.out.print("Enter age: ");
        int age = s.nextInt();

        System.out.print("Enter grade: ");
        char grade = s.next().charAt(0);

        // Create object with initial values
        Student st = new Student(name, age, grade);

        // Display original info
        System.out.println("\nOriginal Information:");
        st.display();

        // Modify using setter methods
        s.nextLine(); // Clear buffer
        System.out.print("\nEnter new name: ");
        String newName = s.nextLine();

        System.out.print("Enter new age: ");
        int newAge = s.nextInt();

        System.out.print("Enter new grade: ");
        char newGrade = s.next().charAt(0);

        // Set new values
        st.setName(newName);
        st.setAge(newAge);
        st.setGrade(newGrade);

        // Display modified info
        System.out.println("\nUpdated Information:");
        st.display();

        s.close();
    }
}
ğŸ” Output Example:
yaml
Copy
Edit
Enter name: Hari
Enter age: 20
Enter grade: A

Original Information:
Name: Hari
Age: 20
Grade: A

Enter new name: Kiran
Enter new age: 21
Enter new grade: B

Updated Information:
Name: Kiran
Age: 21
Grade: B
