You said:
constuctor


ChatGPT said:
A constructor in Java is a special method used to initialize objects when they are created. It has the same name as the class, and doesn't have a return type, not even void.

Let me show you how to use a constructor along with encapsulation to initialize and modify a student's name, age, and grade.

âœ… Example with Constructor and Encapsulation
java
Copy
Edit
import java.util.*;

class Student {
    // private fields (encapsulation)
    private String name;
    private int age;
    private char grade;

    // Constructor to initialize values
    public Student(String name, int age, char grade) {
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
        this.grade = grade;
    }

    // Getters
    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }
    public int getAge() {
        return age;
    }
    public char getGrade() {
        return grade;
    }

    // Setters
    public void setName(String name) {
        this.name = name;
    }
    public void setAge(int age) {
        this.age = age;
    }
    public void setGrade(char grade) {
        this.grade = grade;
    }

    // Display method
    public void display() {
        System.out.println("Name: " + name);
        System.out.println("Age: " + age);
        System.out.println("Grade: " + grade);
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);

        // Read values from user
        System.out.print("Enter name: ");
        String name = s.nextLine();
        System.out.print("Enter age: ");
        int age = s.nextInt();
        System.out.print("Enter grade: ");
        char grade = s.next().charAt(0);

        // Create Student object using constructor
        Student student = new Student(name, age, grade);

        System.out.println("\nOriginal Information:");
        student.display();

        // Modify values using setters
        s.nextLine(); // clear buffer
        System.out.print("\nEnter new name: ");
        String newName = s.nextLine();
        System.out.print("Enter new age: ");
        int newAge = s.nextInt();
        System.out.print("Enter new grade: ");
        char newGrade = s.next().charAt(0);

        // Set new values
        student.setName(newName);
        student.setAge(newAge);
        student.setGrade(newGrade);

        System.out.println("\nUpdated Information:");
        student.display();

        s.close();
    }
}
ğŸ” Key Concepts Used:
Constructor â†’ Student(String name, int age, char grade)

Encapsulation â†’ private fields + get/set methods

Modification â†’ Using setName(), setAge(), setGrade()

Let me know if you want this in Python using __init__() constructor.






